reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a great monitor once attached to a proper stand. The monitor itself is great but the included stand (in the version I got) is very basic, low height and pretty wobbly.I got the VA panel version for my home office as I prefer better contrast (darker blacks) compared to the IPS version.Lateral viewing angles should be better with an IPS screen - that would be better in a brighter office (where the worse contrast of the IPS would not be apparent) and where one might need to colaborate with others looking at the same screen.Videos and pictures look great too. I don't game so the (missing) high refresh rates are not an issue.For some reason I do not see 75Hz available in the OS settings either, only 60Hz. No biggie for office use and watching videos. -- I have figured that out - apparently 75Hz is only available when using lower resolutions, like 1920 x 1080 (useful for gaming, I guess).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent for the price
reviews.reviewText: For the price, a 27" QHD monitor with in-built speakers, two HDMI ports and a full-motion stand by a recognizable brand is simply a steal. This monitor is exactly what I needed and precisely my budget, so to me, this monitor is perfect. 5/5.HOWEVER. I don't think this monitor can be considered perfect; it has thick bezels, the colour accuracy is BAD, the brightness is on the low end, the speakers sound bad and are difficult to set at the right volume, and it has dimer areas at the top of the screen (Either that or the vertical viewing angles are very narrow).BUT, even with all the "bad" I still think this monitor is amazing. It fills a niche. Other 27" monitors are a blurry 1080p mess, or 4k and eye-wateringly expensive; this one is just in between and if you are like me and think 24" is getting small but 32" is an overkill, and that 1080p shouldn't be in anything bigger than a 24, then this monitor is for you!

El MSI PRO MP273QP ha superado mis expectativas en todos los aspectos.Calidad de Imagen Sobresaliente: La resolución WQHD (2560x1440) ofrece una claridad asombrosa. reviews.reviewText: Llegó rápido hasta Colombia, me parece mal que una compra de una pantalla que viene desde tan lejos, solo venga en la caja del producto, he comprado otros productos y vienen protegidos con otras cajas y ademas bolsas de aire, la caja venia rota como si hubiera tenido un golpe (anexo foto) al prenderlo me doy cuenta que tiene muchas fugas de luz y ademas tiene un defecto que se ve cuando la pantalla esta en negro mi decisión es devolverlo, en cuanto la densidad de pixel pues si se nota mucho al ser 1080p se ven los pixels muy grandes.

Es el monitor con mejor relación resolución-tamaño-precio.Por menos de 5k tienes un monitor de 27 pulgadas con resolución de 2160p. Ningún otro monitor de este rango de precios ofrece lo mismo, es a 75Hz pero yo lo uso para trabajar.
